understand about  How to Insert, Add, Replace and Delete Elements in Array(CRUD) - part1

 1: push(): Method that adds one or more elements to the end of an array.
 2: pop(): Method that removes the last element from an array.
 3: unshift(): Method that adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array.
 4: shift(): Method that removes the first element from an array.

 code:-
  // How to Insert, Add, Replace and Delete Elements in Array(CRUD).
let fruits = ["apple","banana","orange"];
console.log(fruits);
fruits.push("mango");
console.log(fruits);
fruits.pop();
console.log(fruits);
console.log(fruits.push("mango"));  // push return number of element here. 
console.log(fruits);
console.log(fruits.unshift("mango"));  // unshift
console.log(fruits); 
console.log(fruits.shift());      // shift
console.log(fruits);


